29/08/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The interior ministry is preparing a plan to fight crime and step up border control, to meet commitments under the Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU. 
According to an article in Monday's (28 August) daily Standard, the plan envisions establishment of new structures to handle the process, as well as training of personnel and improving co-operation among public services to boost efficiency. 
Border protection police and migration police also would be re-organised and supplied with new vehicles, boats and equipment.
In other news, tax authorities shut down the two largest printing houses in the country -- Demokracia and Eurorilindja -- due to their huge debts to the state. 
Eurorilindja prints the ten most influential newspapers in Albania. 
(Albanian News - 29/08/06)
